,"recipeIngredient": [
"2.5 cups shredded Gruyere cheese",
"2.5 cups shredded Emmental cheese",
"2 tablespoons cornstarch",
"1 clove garlic, halved",
"1.5 cups dry white wine",
"1 (8 inch) French bread, cubed",
"1 pound cooked baby potatoes",
"1 cup cornichons",
"1 cup pickled pearl onions" ]
,"recipeInstructions": [
{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"text": "Combine Gruy√®re cheese, Emmental cheese, and cornstarch in a bowl. Mix until the cheese is evenly coated. Set aside."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"text": "Rub the cut side of the garlic all over the inside of a fondue pot or heavy saucepan. Add wine and place over medium heat. Bring to a simmer, then gradually add cheese and cornstarch mixture. Stir with a spatula, gently stirring in a figure-of-eight motion, until all of the cheese is added and the fondue is smooth and homogenous. Reduce heat to medium-low if the fondue is boiling too vigorously."
} ,{
"@type": "HowToStep"
,"text": "Immediately serve fondue, preferably over a warmer. If you used a saucepan on the stove to heat the fondue, you can carefully transfer the fondue to a fondue pot to serve."
} ]
